07.3 TRANSPORT SERVICES
Purchases of transport services are generally
classified by mode of transport. When a ticket
covers two or more modes of transport – for
example, intra-urban bus and underground or
inter-urban train and ferry – and the expenditure cannot be apportioned between them, then
such purchases should be classified in (07.3.5).
Costs of meals, snacks, drinks, refreshments
or accommodation services have to be included
if covered by the fare and not separately priced.
If separately priced, these costs have to be
classified in Division 11.
School transport services are included, but
ambulance services are excluded (06.2.3).
